                    <death when="0559" syriaca-computed-start="0559-01-01" source="#bib1484-1">0559</death>
                    <state type="martyr" source="#bib1484-1">
                        <p>Martyr</p>
                    </state>
                    <note>Fiey provides the following bibliographic citations: <quote source="#bib1484-1">Devos, "Sainte Sirin", 87-131, d'apres Ia version grecque BHG3 , 1637, d'un original
syriaque perdu.
Aussi Devos, dans AB 112 (1994), 4- 31 (avec trad. franr;aise).
BSO, II, 1056- 57 (J. Rabbi).</quote>
                    </note>
                    <note type="abstract" xml:id="abstract-en-1484">In hagiography: Shirin was born in<placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/108">Karka d-Beth Slokh</placeName>to a Zoroastrian family
          but converted to Christianity. She faced great hardship from her family on account of
          this. She was imprisoned and executed.</note>
                    <bibl xml:id="bib1484-1">
                        <title level="m" xml:lang="fr">Saints Syriaques</title>
                        <title level="a" xml:lang="fr">ŠĪRĪN</title>
                        <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/650"/>
                        <citedRange unit="entry">425</citedRange>
                    </bibl>
                    <author>Devos</author>
                    <title>"Sainte Sirin"</title>
                    <citedRange>87-131</citedRange>
                    <note>According to the Greek version BHG3, 1637, from a lost Syriac original</note>
                    <bibl xml:id="bib1484-4">
                        <title>Devos</title>
                        <title> AB</title>
                        <citedRange>112 (1994), 4-31 (with a french translation).</citedRange>
                    </bibl>
